eu.cqse.check.util.clang.misra

Enum EEssentialType

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<EEssentialType>
      • eu.cqse.check.util.clang.misra.EEssentialType
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<EEssentialType>

    public enum EEssentialType
extends java.lang.Enum<EEssentialType>
    Enumeration of the essential types defined by MISRA C2012 Section D.1 The essential-type concept in MISRA is a simplification of the C type system used in the definition of several misra guidelines. It does not apply to C++, only to C (MISRA Cpp2008 defines a different concept of "underlying types" which seems to be incompatible). Do not modify the items of this enum. They are copied verbatim from the MISRA definition. The ordering of the types is important (defines the rank and width of the types in the same category).
